data.name: DuplicateScenarioInReportBuilder
data.value: The given scenario to begin is already present in the current report builder. It may not be begun twice.

data.name: NoMatchingScenarioInReportBuilder
data.value: There is no matching scenario (using the given identity) present in the current report builder.

data.name: ScenarioAlreadyFinalised
data.value: The scenario has already been finalised; no further actions may be taken against it.

data.name: ScenarioNotFinalisedYet
data.value: The scenario has not yet been finalised; you must execute '{0}' first to finalise the scenario.

data.name: PerformableWasRequiredInBuilderStack
data.value: Whilst building a report about a specific `{0}', an attempt to get the corresponding `{1}' failed to find any performances. This scenario is invalid.

data.name: PerformableDoesNotMatchExpectedPerformance
data.value: Whilst building a report about a specific `{0}', an attempt to get the corresponding `{1}' failed because the {1} was for a different {0}.

data.name: ReportableMustBeGainAbilityOrPerformance
data.value: The reportable item to write must represent either an actor gaining an ability or a performance.

data.name: TracableEventIdMustBePositiveInteger
data.value: The trace event ID must be a positive integer.
